---
source: plasm-oss/crates/plasm-core/src/prompt_render.rs
expression: prompt
---
# This defines valid Plasm syntax for this prompt; reply with one valid plasm_program:
#
# Output:
# - Single `plasm_expr` iff one lookup/query/search/relation/method/action is the whole answer.
# - Else one multi-line `plasm_program`: bind → narrow (projection/postfix/bracket-render) → small bare roots—not many one-line tool calls.
#
# Grammar (pseudo-EBNF; DOMAIN rows instantiate `plasm_expr` atoms):
# plasm_program ::= plasm_roots | binding+ plasm_roots
# binding       ::= ident "=" plasm_node
# plasm_roots   ::= plasm_return ("," plasm_return)*
# plasm_return  ::= node_ref | plasm_expr
# plasm_node    ::= ( plasm_expr | node_ref ) postfix* bracket_render_tail? | node_ref "=>" plasm_value | node_ref "=>" effect_expr
# plasm_expr    ::= entity_expr [projection]
# entity_expr   ::= query_all | get | query | relation | method | create_action
# query_all     ::= e#
# get           ::= e#(id) or e#(p#=v, p#=v)
# query         ::= e#{p#=v, …}
# relation      ::= e#(id).p#
# method        ::= e#(id).m#() or e#(id).m#(p#=v,..)
# create_action ::= e#.m#(args)
# projection    ::= e#(id)[p#,…] | "[" fields "]"
# postfix       ::= transform | "[" fields "]"
# bracket_render_tail ::= ( "[" fields "]" )? "<<TAG" heredoc_body "TAG"
# positive_int  ::= non-zero decimal integer literal
# agg_func      ::= "sum" | "avg" | "min" | "max"
# agg_spec      ::= ident "=" ( "count" | agg_func "(" field ")" )
# agg_specs     ::= agg_spec ("," agg_spec)*
# sort_dir      ::= omitted | "desc" | "asc" | "ascending" | "descending"
# transform     ::= ".limit(" positive_int ")" | ".sort(" field ["," sort_dir] ")" | ".aggregate(" agg_specs ")" | ".group_by(" field "," agg_specs ")" | ".singleton()" | ".page_size(" positive_int ")"
# fields        ::= [p#,…]
# plasm_value   ::= literal | node_ref | node_ref.field | _.field | [v, …]
# effect_expr   ::= taught write/update/delete/action surface from DOMAIN (same line may template rows)
# ident/node_ref/field ::= agent-chosen names for bound nodes and fields
# literal       ::= quoted string | number | bool | null | heredoc
#
# Aggregates (examples): `.aggregate(n=count)`, `.aggregate(total=sum(amount), lo=min(price))`, `.group_by(author, n=count)`.
#
# Continuation:
# - Postfix (transforms, `[fields]`, `<<TAG…TAG`) may chain on one surface `plasm_expr`.
# - `ident.<relation>` only after surface row bindings (get/query/relation); after projection/transform/`=>`, repeat full DOMAIN expr or rebind. Bracket-render = Minijinja `rows`; optional `[fields]` narrows columns → row `{"content":"…"}` — use **`binding.content`** for string/body args.
#
# MCP `program` (JSON string):
# - Literal U+000A between statements (one `ident = …` per line; bare roots last). Spaces never separate statements.
# - Heredoc: newline after `<<TAG` opener; close line trims to `TAG` / `TAG)` / `TAG,` / `TAG}`; first matching trimmed interior line closes—opaque `TAG` for blobs. Commas inside heredocs never split roots (e.g. `…<<B` / `Hello` / `B` / `), e2`).
#
# Discipline:
# - Plan shape first; small roots unless raw rows requested; bracket-render row-derived text, static `<<TAG` for fixed payloads.
# - `page(sN_pgM)` continues a chosen list only; DOMAIN is the shape contract—no probe calls.
#
# DOMAIN / catalogue:
# - `plasm_expr` = atoms; `Meaning` = how to pick/fill—never paste `Meaning`. Bare comma-separated roots (no `return`); every symbol taught here.
# - Projection: minimal non-empty `[p#,…]`; identity row lists full fields once. Leading `p#` rows = slot metadata when method `args:` is insufficient.
# - e#, m#, p# are session-local aliases — copy them exactly; new prompts supersede old meanings.
# - Pick by `Meaning`, copy `plasm_expr`, bind keyed slot (`p12=value`) only; never positional or renumbered args.
# - Instantiate grammar lines from DOMAIN only; keyed `p#=v` never positional. `v=$` in tables is a fill cue.
# - `e#{p#=v, …}` / `e#` list/filter; `e#(id) or e#(p#=v, p#=v)` fetch one; `e#(id).p#` relate; `e#(id).m#() or e#(id).m#(p#=v,..)` call; `e#.m#(args)` without id; `e#(id)[p#,…]` projects—after `e#(id)`, `.` is relation or taught `m#` only.
# - Scoped child lists: `X{p#=AnchorEntity(id)}` from the child entity’s DOMAIN rows; never invent `Y(id).p#`.
# - Arrays in args: `[v, …]` (e.g. `p#=[e#($)]`). Quoted strings: only `\"` and `\\` escapes.
# - `select` one allowed value; `multiselect` / multi-value lists as `[v, …]`.
# - `markdown`/`html`/`document`/`json_text`/`blob` values (per `Meaning`): `<<TAG` … `TAG` only; e.g. `m#(..., p#=<<TXT` + newline body + `TXT` newline `)`.
# - `p#`-only rows declare slots (metadata), not expressions to emit.
# - `$` marks fill-ins — substitute real values; never send `$`.
# - `..` — optional trailing params (`optional params:` lists them); `..` alone means all args optional.
#

plasm_expr	Meaning
p4	uuid · id
p3	markdown · body
e1($)[p4,p3]	returns e1 · A comment on an issue.
e1.m1(p2=e3($), p1=$)	returns e1 · args: p2 issue ref:e3 req; p1 body markdown req · Add a markdown comment on an issue.
e1	returns [e1] · List comments.
e1($).p5	returns e3 · Issue this comment belongs to.
p8	uuid · id
p9	float · Cycle index within the team (Linear exposes as a number).
p10	str · Cycle start (ISO-8601 timestamp from the API).
p7	str · Cycle end (ISO-8601 timestamp from the API).
e2($)[p8,p9,p10,p7,team]	returns e2 · A time-boxed iteration on a team (sprint / cycle window).
e2{p6=e6($)}	returns [e2] · args: p6 team ref:e6 req · List iteration cycles for a team (ordered by the API).
e2($).p11	returns e6 · Team this cycle belongs to.
p32	uuid · id
p31	str · Human-visible key (e.g. ENG-42).
p33	str · title
p30	markdown · description
e3($)[p32,p31,p33,p30,parent,team,project,assignee,state,cycle]	returns e3 · A Linear issue (task, bug, or feature).
e3($).m9()	returns e3 · Move an issue to trash (recoverable; not a permanent delete).
e3($).m13()	returns e3 · args: p29 title str opt; p25 description markdown opt; p27 project ref:e5 opt; p23 assignee ref:e7 opt; p28 state ref:e8 opt; p26 parent ref:e3 opt; p24 cycle ref:e2 opt · Update an issue
e3($).m6(p12=e4($))	returns e3 · args: p12 label ref:e4 req · Attach one label to this issue (existing labels kept).
e3.m8(p20=e6($), p21=$,..)	returns e3 · args: p20 team ref:e6 req; p21 title str req; p16 description markdown opt; p18 project ref:e5 opt; p14 assignee ref:e7 opt; p19 state ref:e8 opt; p17 parent ref:e3 opt; p15 cycle ref:e2 opt · Create a new issue on a team, optionally in a project, column, cycle, or under a parent issue.
e3($).m12(p22=e4($))	returns e3 · args: p22 label ref:e4 req · Remove one label from this issue.
e3{p13=e6($)}	returns [e3] · args: p13 team ref:e6 req · List issues for a specific team.
e3	returns [e3] · List issues in the workspace.
e3($).p40	returns e7 · User assigned to the issue.
e3($).p35	returns [e3] · Sub-issues nested directly under this issue in the work hierarchy.
e3($).p34	returns e2 · Iteration cycle when the issue is scheduled into one.
e3($).p37	returns [e4] · Labels on this issue.
e3($).p36	returns e3 · Parent issue when this issue is a sub-issue (otherwise absent).
e3($).p38	returns e5 · Project this issue belongs to.
e3($).p41	returns e8 · Current workflow state.
e3($).p39	returns e6 · Owning team.
p50	uuid · id
p51	str · name
p49	str · color
e4($)[p50,p51,p49]	returns e4 · An issue label.
e4($).m17()	returns e4 · args: p48 name str opt; p46 color str opt; p47 description markdown opt · Update label name, color, or description.
e4.m14(p44=$,..)	returns e4 · args: p44 name str req; p45 team ref:e6 opt; p42 color str opt; p43 description markdown opt · Create an issue label (optionally scoped to a team; omit team for workspace-wide).
e4	returns [e4] · List issue labels.
p55	uuid · id
p56	str · name
p57	str · Stable slug for the project within its team.
e5($)[p55,p56,p57]	returns e5 · A Linear project within a team.
e5.m18(p53=$, p54=e6($),..)	returns e5 · args: p53 name str req; p54 team ref:e6 req; p52 description markdown opt · Create a project owned by one or more teams.
e5	returns [e5] · List projects.
p58	uuid · id
p60	str · name
p59	str · Short key (e.g. ENG).
e6($)[p58,p60,p59]	returns e6 · A Linear team (workspace grouping).
e6	returns [e6] · List teams.
p63	uuid · id
p64	str · name
p61	str · displayName
p62	str · email
e7($)[p63,p64,p61,p62]	returns e7 · A Linear user.
e7	returns [e7] · List users.
p72	uuid · id
p73	str · name
p75	str · State category (e.g. started, completed).
p74	float · position
e8($)[p72,p73,p75,p74]	returns e8 · A workflow column/state for a team (backlog, in progress, done, …).
e8.m25(p67=$, p70=e6($), p69=$, p65=$,..)	returns e8 · args: p67 name str req; p70 team ref:e6 req; p69 state_type str req; p65 color str req; p66 description markdown opt; p68 position float opt · Create a workflow column on a team.
e8{p71=e6($)}	returns [e8] · args: p71 team ref:e6 req · List workflow columns for a team—column title, category (e.g. backlog, in progress, done), and …
